query.result:
49 “Oh, do not contend with the dry scab
50 that discolors me, the skin,
51 nor to the lack of flesh that I have;

52 but tell me the truth of you, say who those are
53 two souls that there make escort to you;
54 do not remain that you do not speak to me!”

58 Therefore tell me, by God, what causes you to be so thin;
59 do not make me speak while I marvel,
60 because he can hardly speak who is full of another desire.

